parameters: Clea (If you don't talk to Prince Lex)
Clea (If you don't talk to the guild leader)

Guild Leader Agonia: Just now, we received a formal request
from the noble Kasaro regarding the transportation of a
giant crystal.

Guild Leader Agonia: We will split into three groups and
head towards the noble Kasaro's retirement home, our
destination.

Shimosu from the Unknown Night: It's probably a talk about
dispersing the risk of troublesome matters, right?

Shimosu from the Unknown Night: It seems like something a
stingy noble would think of.

Stolge of Affection: This is a request from the client to
transport a high-value package, there is no reason to
refuse.

Guild Leader Agonia: The squad led by Shimosu will take the
route through Varie and Kanonas.

Guild Leader Agonia: The squad led by Celis will take the
route through the noble Kasaro's estate, passing through
Oros.
Guild Leader Agonia: I will go through Mucos and Fotizona.

Stolge of Affection: I have a relationship with the client
who is heading to the destination ahead of me, but this is
an absolutely crucial request that cannot afford to fail.
Guild Leader Agonia: Do you have any questions?
Clea: Um... no, I will talk to you separately later.

Guild Leader Agonia: Let's meet at the noble Kasaro's
estate. We must uphold the three principles and make sure to
arrive there safely without fail.

Guild Leader Agonia: You seemed like you were about to say
something. Is there something wrong?

Clea: Actually, I fought against thieves at Lord Luid's
mansion, and they seemed to know about the crystal
transportation.

Clea: I don't want to think about it, but maybe the
information is leaking from somewhere.

Stolge of Affection: Did you all notice too? I was assigned
to enter the site ahead of time for that reason.

Stolge of Affection: I hate to say it, but please keep this
matter confidential. I want to believe that there are no
traitors in the guild... but I can't help but think
otherwise.

Guild Leader Agonia: Do you know the identity of the
thieves?
Clea: They called themselves the Aspida Alliance.

Guild Leader Agonia: A group plotting the revival of Valt...
They are a bunch of outlaws collecting crystals and
legendary weapons, aren't they?

Guild Leader Agonia: I will leave the investigation of this
matter to Stolge. Clea, please head to Oros.
Celis of the Swift Wind: Understood, Guild Leader.
Celis of the Swift Wind: Everyone, let's go.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Oros Region/The Mountain City
of Oros\c[0]

Guild Leader Agonia: I think everyone will arrive in just a
little while.

Guild Leader Agonia: Clea, how do you see Prince Lex? You
should have witnessed the moment he changed.

Clea: I can't express it well, but it felt more like he
returned to his original self rather than undergoing a
change.

Clea: I felt that the current state is actually the essence
of Prince Lex.

Guild Leader Agonia: I see... It was said that his father
also had a monster in his heart.

Guild Leader Agonia: The issue is where the fangs of that
monster he keeps in his heart will be directed.

Guild Leader Agonia: It seems that everyone has arrived.
Let's hold a meeting to decide the future of the
Adventurer's Guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: It seems that Prince Lex is moving
towards reclaiming the throne. He told us to choose whether
we are on the side of the prince or the queen.

Simos of the Unknown Night: What kind of authority are you
giving orders with? We're supposed to be an organization
that doesn't belong to anyone and isn't commanded.

Simos of the Unknown Night: That should have been the last
testament of the previous... old hag.

Stolge of Affection: I generally agree with Simos. I would
like Agonia to explain why she called for this meeting.

Stolge of Affection: To be honest, I don't think the
Prince's faction is capable of opposing Queen Caron. They
seem like a motley crew.

Guild Leader Agonia: Prince Lex has successfully managed to
drag the noble Pido from the Senate into the prince's
faction.

Guild Leader Agonia: The situation has dramatically changed.
Prince Lex is seriously determined to take the throne from
Caron.

Swift Celis: Does Prince Lex, who has the Imperial Army on
Queen Caron's side, have any plans?

Stolge of Affection: Perhaps that's who we are. Both Lex
and Caron should definitely want to avoid a civil war.

Stolge of Affection: While mercenaries may gather in
numbers, we need a small but elite force that can resist the
Imperial Secret Service.

Simos of the Unknown Night: If you ask me, it's reckless at
best. I don't know what kind of plan Lex has, but it's a
reckless move.

Guild Leader Agonia: I also think so. At this point, there
is no chance of winning on Lex's side.

Simos of the Unknown Night: Seems like I'll get drunk
tonight if I get along with you.

Stolge of Affection: Clea, what do you think? I've heard
that you were in the midst of the turmoil.

Clea: I don't understand much about politics, but I believe
Queen Caron is a dangerous person.

Clea: There is a high possibility that she is conspiring
with the sorceress Eratoma to create a new dragon.

Clea: If a dragon is born, it will definitely become a
threat. I want to stop it to prevent the creation of beings
like me.

Simos of the Unknown Night: The birth of a dragon, huh?
Seems like there are a lot of things I don't know.

Guild Leader Agonia: Let's organize the situation again and
share the information that each of us has.

Guild Leader Agonia: It's been quite some time. Shall we
come to a conclusion soon?

Guild Leader Agonia: I have decided to cooperate with Prince
Lex.

Guild Leader Agonia: As a condition, I will ensure that no
interference from any authority is made to maintain the
organization if he becomes the king.

Guild Leader Agonia: Prince Lex may have many unknown
aspects, but at this point, I have determined that Queen
Caron is more dangerous.

Simos of the Unknown Night: Agonia... What will you do if
they interfere after Lex wins?

Guild Leader Agonia: At that time, until we fight against
King Lex, no one will interfere. That's why we are
adventurers' guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: The Adventurers' Guild, Futral's Wing,
is a symbol of freedom. No one should be allowed to break
these wings.

Guild Leader Agonia: We should be a group that fights for
that purpose and is willing to risk our lives for it.

Guild Leader Agonia: This is a decision made by the guild
leader! From today onwards, we will raise our flag against
the rulers of time.

Guild Leader Agonia: Clea, please go and inform Prince Lex
about this.

Guild Leader Agonia: I will give instructions to each of
you. Please be cautious of the fact that the enemy is
already moving.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Guild Leader Agonia: I will have Clea pave the way.
Clea: Understood. Should we aim for the Photizona Palace?

Guild Leader Agonia: That's right, Atu should be waiting for
us at the front.

Thief Nora: You're really going all out...!? Ugh... just
imagining it makes my body tremble.
Priestess Sophia: I see... Are we going to be the decoys?

Mage Relm: Huh, is that so!? Wait, I can't agree with that
at all!

Guild Leader Agonia: Atu's aim is to flank and annihilate
the Prince's faction, including us, in front of the palace.

Guild Leader Agonia: The other combatants will eliminate
everyone except for Atu's team. I want Clea and the others
to buy us some time.

Guild Leader Agonia: Above all, he desires strong opponents
and will fight without any tricks. I have determined that
Clea and the others are the ones who can stop Atu with our
current forces.

Clea: I think we can endure... but it might be difficult for
us to take them down on our own.

Clea: I have personally experienced the same kind of
pressure as facing a dragon when I crossed swords with such
a monster.

Guild Leader Agonia: It is my job to checkmate everyone
until the check.
Guild Leader Agonia: I will ambush and kill Atu.

Guild Leader Agonia: I want a momentary opening. Please keep
Atu engaged in battle for that purpose.
Clea: ...Is that really okay, Guild Leader?

Guild Leader Agonia: This is the bond of trust between him
and me. We won't betray each other, lie, or run away.

Guild Leader Agonia: I will only fulfill my role. Please let
me know when you are ready.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Guild Leader Agonia: Are you ready to go?
Clea: Please give me a little more time to prepare.

Guild Leader Agonia: Please prepare thoroughly, but
understand that we don't have much time.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Guild Leader Agonia: Please go through the Fotizona Avenue.
There should be some grunts there, but you don't have to
engage with them.
Guild Leader Agonia: Please be careful.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Stolge: I'll leave that to you.

Stolge of Affection: It's become quite a situation, hasn't it?
Really.

Stolge of Affection: Picking a fight with the Empire... Haha, if
I told my past self that, they would probably faint.

Celis, the Gale: This might be a big job since the dragon
subjugation. There's a possibility that we might not be able
to see some people anymore.

Celis, the Gale: That's why we must survive no matter what.
If we're not alive, we won't be able to protect anyone.
Guild Leader Agonia: First, we have a report from Stolge.

Stolge of Affection: I went to the Monimos Highlands with
General Atu... it was hell.

Stolge of Affection: We are based in a nearby garrison
where I have never seen such well-coordinated goblins and
orcs. However, there is a possibility that it may be
breached.

Stolge of Affection: There are even stories of seeing
ogres... right now, the Monimos Highlands are the most
dangerous place in the empire.

Clea: I heard before that the ones leading the goblins are
led by orcs, and the ones leading the orcs are ogres.

Clea: Then, who is leading the ogres...? I think it's a
dragon. That guy must be there for sure.
Guild Leader Agonia: Has the dragon been sighted?

Stolge of Affection: No... I haven't heard about that, but
it seems they have concluded that there is a possibility of
it being near the summit.

Stolge of Affection: Even if that were true, if it's near
the summit, we won't be able to reach it.

Guild Leader Agonia: The Monimos Mountains is the tallest
mountain in the empire. If there is a dragon at the summit,
it would be impossible to reach.

Guild Leader Agonia: If we're going to fight, the only
option is to bring the dragon down to the ground.

Guild Leader Agonia: The situation on site hasn't changed,
so Stolge, please proceed with supporting Shimos.

Stolge of Affection: I understand... It's been a while
since I felt so reluctant to go this far.

Guild Leader Agonia: We must think of a solution to bring
down the dragon and resolve this difficult problem.

Guild Leader Agonia: ...We've been discussing, but we
haven't come up with a good solution, have we?

Mage Relm: The conditions are too harsh! It's impossible for
us to climb up, and we don't even know how to drag it down.

Mage Relm: This is not just a difficult problem, it's an
impossible one!
Thief Nora: H-How about luring it with food...?

Cleric Sophia: If it's me or Nora-chan, we could easily lure
it out with bread and wine.

Clea: If we can lure it out with something... If we defeat
the goblins, will it come down?

Receptionist Piste: Everyone! Since you must be tired, let's
refresh ourselves with some tea!

Receptionist Piste: It seems like we're having quite a
difficult time, huh?

Swift Celis: ...We don't have any good ideas and it's
frustrating.

Receptionist Piste: Don't make that face! Not everyone can
solve everything like a hero, you know.

Receptionist Piste: By the way... There was a legend of a
hero slaying a dragon, right?
Receptionist Piste: Using a tamed giant bird... umm...

Swift Celis: The dragon that ravages the village and escapes
to the mountaintop... The hero provoked and lured out the
dragon using a giant bird.

Swift Celis: The dragon's lair is Mount Monimos... the stage
of the myth of the dragon slayer!
Thief Nora: I-It's amazing! Let's go with the same method!

Mage Relm: How are we going to prepare a giant bird?! It
might be even more difficult than climbing Mount Monimos!

Priestess Sophia: If only we could attract the dragon's
attention... something big that can fly in the sky.

Clea: I'm going to meet with Kasaro-san. How about we use
the airship and make it resemble a giant bird?

Guild Leader Agonia: ...It's decided then. Clea, please
negotiate with Mr. Kasaro.

Guild Leader Agonia: We can expect a tough battle, so please
make sure to prepare for it without neglecting anything.
Guild Leader Agonia: Well then, let's disband for now.

Prince Rex: I was able to make it here today thanks to the
Adventurer's Guild.

Prince Rex: I will express my gratitude properly after
becoming king.

Prince Rex: The real battle will be after I become king. The
palace is inhabited by demons, just like the previous kings,
and I...

Prince Rex: Above all, I must fight not only against demons,
but also against the monster hidden within myself that needs
to be conquered in order to achieve victory.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Prince Rex: Finally, we will infiltrate the royal palace.

Prince Rex: I have high expectations for your work. Please
help me pave the way to the throne.

Fushichiya's Shimosu: 'We are adventurers who fight for
ourselves. Risk your lives for the future of the guild and
Futeira.'

Receptionist Piste: Things are progressing rapidly, and
before we know it, we'll end up infiltrating the royal
palace...

Receptionist Piste: I can only offer my support, but I'll be
praying for everyone's safe return!

Prince Rex: I am grateful for Casaro's cooperation in
securing the support of the guild and for stalling them as I
have heard of their achievements from my vassals.

Guild Leader Agonia: The real battle starts now. If we don't
defeat Caron, everything has a high chance of becoming our
enemy.

Prince Rex: That's right, if we don't win, we'll lose
everything. I must show the power to defeat Caron.

Guild Leader Agonia: It's raining now, which might be
somewhat convenient for us.

Prince Rex: I want you to gather those who will participate
in the operation. There is something I must convey to
everyone.

Prince Rex: First of all, I would like to thank you all for
choosing someone legitimate rather than an evil person.

Prince Rex: According to the information, they are planning
to obstruct our justice not only with the dark forces but
also with monsters.

Prince Rex: However, with me and all of you, we will
eliminate Caron and his gang from the royal palace, and
Fotizona will be reborn as an empire of order and justice
once again.

Prince Rex: I am the guarantee! As long as I am the king,
the empire's order and justice will never waver!

Prince Rex: I will personally enter the royal palace and
defeat Caron.

Prince Rex: It is said that even during the founding of the
kingdom, there was a thunderstorm like today.

Prince Rex: The previous kings themselves wielded swords and
headed to the battlefield! When the rain clears, the throne
will be vacant for the rightful person!

Prince Rex: Brave warriors! Seasoned heroes! I will lead the
way! Grasp your swords!

Prince Rex: The sword I wield will pave the way! The one who
sits on the throne shall be the legitimate and new king,
Rex!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
